{{notelist|n}}

== Trivia ==

* When the {{code|item}} property displays a block, its model appears rotated and cull facing still applies as if it was not rotated.
** The only block that is not affected by this is the [[How did we get here? (block)|How did we get here?]] block, but only when the {{code|item}} property is set to 0.
* Tint blocks and items like the [[grass block]] and [[spawn egg]]s always appear with a white tint when displayed by the block.
* Translucent blocks and items are opaque when displayed by the block.
* Some block entities don't display by the block, such as chests, beds, heads, etc...
* The enchanted glint does not appear on items that have the enchanted glint when displayed by the block.
** Because of that, enchanted golden apple when displayed by the block looks like normal golden apple.
